robeger wrote:
&gt; So seeing a docs processed per second rate of less than 1 is normal? 
&gt; (that&#39;s what I was seeing before I stopped it)

It depends. Even though you&#39;ve started with 20-something sites, if
many of them are small, they&#39;ll finish early and then you&#39;ll only
be left with a handful of sites with pending resources. If the sites
are then slow, or you are being very polite, you might only be visiting
a site (or less) per second.

When the crawler seems slow, use Reports-&gt;Frontier Report to see how
many per-host work queues are active. I would never expect the progress
to be more than (# active queues)/(minimum delay seconds).

&gt; Maybe I have my politeness settings too polite and it&#39;s slowing me
&gt; down too much.  What are your recommended settings?

The defaults are a good start. We go even more polite if we can.
If you&#39;re confident the sites are able to handle the traffic you can
edge down the retry-delay multiple,min-delay and max-delay settings...
but patience is a virtue if you don&#39;t want to anger (and sometimes
get IP-blocked by) crawled sites.

- Gordon @ IA




